        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Glenrhydding House | Patterdale, Penrith</placeName>
                    <date>June 8<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1881.</date>
                    <salute>My dear D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Gilbert</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. be the most ungrateful of men, if I were not greatly pleased by your letter. I beg you to thank M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Lawes most cordially for his most kind invitation.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> It would have given me real pleasure to have accepted it, &amp; I have always felt much curiosity to inspect the very interesting work at Harpenden; but in truth I have not strength enough to visit at any house. All that I could do, w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. be to come to Harpenden &amp; be introduced to M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Lawes, which I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. very much like, walk about for an hour &amp; see your plots &amp; then return to London for the night— As it is we shall not leave this place until next month.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> Therefore I must forego this to me great pleasure.</p>
<p>Once again allow me to thank heartily M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Lawes &amp; yourself for your most kind proposal, &amp; believe me, dear D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Gilbert | Yours very sincerely | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 Glenrhydding … Penrith] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘<hi rend="italic">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi>’ </note>
            </div>
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13196.xml">letter from J. H. Gilbert, 5 June 1881</ref> and n. 1. <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2834.xml">John Bennet Lawes</ref> had founded the experimental agricultural station on his Rothamsted estate at Harpenden, near St Albans, Hertfordshire.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">The Darwins visited Patterdale in the Lake District from 3 June to 4 July 1881 (<ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1218.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Emma Darwin’s</ref> diary (DAR 242)).</note>     
        </div>
    
